# SVG Convention

## Where SVGs live

| SVG type | Location | Method |
|---|---|---|
| Developer-controlled artwork (logos, decorative graphics, dividers) | `src/assets/` | `?raw` import + `set:html` |
| Favicon | `public/favicon.svg` | `<link>` in Layout head |
| CMS-managed images (client logos, content images) | Prismic media library | `<img>` with URL from Prismic |
| Tiny one-off icons (hamburger, arrows, chevrons) | Inline in the component | Paste SVG markup directly |

## Standard pattern: `?raw` + `set:html`

```astro
---
import artworkSvg from '../../assets/my-graphic.svg?raw';
---

<div class="artwork" set:html={artworkSvg} />
```

Style the inlined SVG with scoped CSS:

```css
.artwork :global(svg) {
  width: 100%;
  height: auto;
  fill: currentColor;
}
```

## Security: `set:html` and trusted sources only

`set:html` injects raw HTML â€” including `<script>` tags if present. **Only use it with SVGs you control** (i.e. files committed to `src/assets/`). Never pipe user-uploaded, CMS-authored, or otherwise untrusted SVG content through `set:html`. For CMS images, use `<img>` which sandboxes the content.
